  "texts": [
    "Limited Cognitive Capacity: Individuals have a limited capacity for processing information and cannot realistically grasp all possible alternatives or consequences when making decisions.",
    "Cognitive constraints may prompt the adoption of heuristic mental shortcuts, which can be efficient but also prone to errors.",
    "The impact of cognitive load is significant in complex tasks where the individual must hold multiple pieces of information in working memory while attempting to discern relevant patterns or implications. 3.",
    "Limited Time: Individuals must make decisions within certain time constraints, meaning they cannot always analyze every option thoroughly.",
    "The advantage of having more time permits a more comprehensive collection of information and analysis, leading to more deliberate decisions."
  ],
